Thank you for your review ~ 
The reason for this title is that the metric of the survival status of nodes is to describe whether they are online in terms of 0 and 1, so if there are multiple nodes on the graph, their polylines will coincide. So if you want to observe its survival status, you need to click on the properties of the corresponding node below, so that you can display only the polyline of the selected node.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/71131924/183789995-c15ec0e0-da82-4e64-b881-014b510c676d.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/71131924/183790220-fe614019-b6eb-4c6b-b72d-10d75458df2b.png)
Besides, please update doc of new metrics at the some time.

Get it, but I think the title of panel should describe the meaning of the data in this panel instead of a operation description. So may be the title can be "The status of cluster node" and set a value mapping(0 -> "unknown", 1 -> "survive"), see: https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/panels/format-data/
